<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="a4aa6091-6f3e-5746-ba2e-83564033b314" activityNameId="f62088fb-61f0-4c88-b192-abfa110d415f" parentActivityId="2f3bbe16-54e2-49a3-ac82-abfa11eeecde" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of waste glass, unsanitary landfill, very wet infiltration class (1000mm)</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to air via landfill gas, and to water via leachate.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'waste glass' in an unsanitary landfill. Recommended use of this dataset: for waste material going to unsanitary landfill in a very wet water infiltration class location, as part of unsorted, unmanaged, unscavenged municipal waste mixture. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% glass. Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 0.1423 MJ/kg; net heating value 0.04602 MJ/kg; H2O 20000; O 483070; H na; C na; S na; N na; P na; B na; Cl 195.89; Br na; F na; I na; Ag na; As na; Ba na; Cd na; Co na; Cr 303.63; Cu 7.8356; Hg na; Mn na; Mo na; Ni na; Pb 38.688; Sb na; Se na; Sn na; V na; Zn 3.9178; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si 359090; Fe na; Ca 72818; Al na; K na; Mg na; Na 64472. Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 60.4%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 1%. 0.356 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="9a63625a-358b-4c1d-bf95-50ba038a759b">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents a landfill of 'infiltration class 5 very wet'. Landfill site with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 8 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 1900 mm/year, and net infiltration of 1000 mm/year. Temperature at site can result in permafrost conditions, which slows down water flow by a factor of (alpha t) 0.999. Total climate adjustments with alpha pt of 0.999. The leachate percolating through the landfill has an average residence time of 3.75 years.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Reference for climatic parameters: Doka, G., 2018, Inventory parameters for regionalised waste disposal mixes</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is an inventory for an unsanitary, sub-controlled landfill for municipal solid waste. Ultimate average landfill height is 15 meters. Operation phase duration is 25 years. The total, waste-specific raw landfill gas mass produced in the landfill is 0.004685 kg. The total CH4 mass in the raw landfill gas is 0 kg. Percentage of landfill gas directly emitted is 100w%. Leachate of the landfill is not treated, but emitted untreated. Based on average waste composition and chosen climate data the end of carbonate phase is estimated to be reached 1733 years after waste deposition.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2006-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
